    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but why does it matter if it's just a symptom? it feels so much more honest than the act i'm putting on every day. if the \"real me\" is already gone, then the person everyone sees is just a lie. it feels like i'm just wasting breath pretending to be someone i'm not. doesn't it seem a bit pointless to keep up the charade when there's nobody actually home?",
